summary: Detective Pikachu Team Shares Why They Went With Photorealistic Pokemon
title: Detective Pikachu Team Shares Why They Went With Photorealistic Pokemon
body:
Detective Pikachu Team Shares Why They Went With Photorealistic Pokemon

Credit: Warner Bros

Detective Pikachu looks like its going to be a lot of fun for Pokemon fans.

With two excellent trailers, we’ve been treated to a variety of live-action Pokemon. Now there was a lot of question on how they would be presented, the photorealistic versions have caused a stir amongst fans. They love it, hate it, or are split. Though, largely, it tends to be more in the “love it”…

tags: this is a joke post by the way
summary: So some more clips for the Detective Pikachu movie were released on twitter earlier (and I think taken down for some reason?)....
body:
So some more clips for the Detective Pikachu movie were released on twitter earlier (and I think taken down for some reason?).

“Sweet mother of Arceus” is an actual in-universe expression in this movie.

I don’t know whether to find that amusing… or wonder where the heck that expression came from, considering Arceus is described in-universe as “The original one” and I’m pretty sure there’s no canonical Jesus equivalent to go along with it (Anyone who says Mew or whatever… there’s nothing really linking the two together in the games, even if you do want to go with the “Ancestor of all Pokémon” theory). So by extension, there shouldn’t be a Virgin Mary equivalent either.

So what possible context is there for “Mother of Arceus” being a thing?

Am I overthinking this?
